The paper presents an algorithm for estimating the cardinality of a set through random sampling, which is a common problem in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The algorithm uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.AI) to achieve its results. Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between the number of samples and the accuracy of the estimate, which is a common theme in statistical learning (cs.LG).
